{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775850377330,"sessionID":"ses_287124991ffeRjQmm9oDsFsSrT","part":{"id":"prt_d78ee4c46001AeoE819BYQJ77P","messageID":"msg_d78ee1db5001iEpIZ7nMm728Rz","sessionID":"ses_287124991ffeRjQmm9oDsFsSrT","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-a9b0b90d1d254819b98bc3d97221423e","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/deployment/client-go.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/deployment/client-go.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # client-go library\n2: \n3: Generated Kubernetes client code for API group **`runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` / `v1alpha1`**, module path **`github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go`**. Source reference: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/client-go/`.\n4: \n5: ## Clientset\n6: \n7: ### `Interface` (`clientset/versioned/clientset.go`)\n8: \n9: ```go\n10: type Interface interface {\n11: \tDiscovery() discovery.DiscoveryInterface\n12: \tRuntimeV1alpha1() runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Interface\n13: }\n14: ```\n15: \n16: ### `Clientset` struct\n17: \n18: Embeds `*discovery.DiscoveryClient` and holds `runtimeV1alpha1 *runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Client`.\n19: \n20: **Constructors**\n21: \n22: - `NewForConfig(c *rest.Config) (*Clientset, error)`\n23: - `NewForConfigAndClient(c *rest.Config, httpClient *http.Client) (*Clientset, error)`\n24: - `NewForConfigOrDie(c *rest.Config) *Clientset`\n25: - `New(c rest.Interface) *Clientset`\n26: \n27: **Group accessor:** `RuntimeV1alpha1() runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Interface`\n28: \n29: ---\n30: \n31: ## Typed client — `runtime/v1alpha1`\n32: \n33: ### `RuntimeV1alpha1Interface` (`clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/runtime_client.go`)\n34: \n35: ```go\n36: type RuntimeV1alpha1Interface interface {\n37: \tRESTClient() rest.Interface\n38: \tAgentRuntimesGetter\n39: \tCodeInterpretersGetter\n40: }\n41: ```\n42: \n43: `RuntimeV1alpha1Client` implements this interface. REST defaults: `GroupVersion` = `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1`.SchemeGroupVersion, `APIPath` = `/apis`, negotiated serializer from `clientset/versioned/scheme`.\n44: \n45: ### `AgentRuntimesGetter` / `AgentRuntimeInterface` (`.../agentruntime.go`)\n46: \n47: ```go\n48: type AgentRuntimesGetter interface {\n49: \tAgentRuntimes(namespace string) AgentRuntimeInterface\n50: }\n51: \n52: type AgentRuntimeInterface interface {\n53: \tCreate(ctx context.Context, agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, opts metav1.CreateOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n54: \tUpdate(ctx context.Context, agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, opts metav1.UpdateOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n55: \tUpdateStatus(ctx context.Context, agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, opts metav1.UpdateOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n56: \tDelete(ctx context.Context, name string, opts metav1.DeleteOptions) error\n57: \tDeleteCollection(ctx context.Context, opts metav1.DeleteOptions, listOpts metav1.ListOptions) error\n58: \tGet(ctx context.Context, name string, opts metav1.GetOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n59: \tList(ctx context.Context, opts metav1.ListOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeList, error)\n60: \tWatch(ctx context.Context, opts metav1.ListOptions) (watch.Interface, error)\n61: \tPatch(ctx context.Context, name string, pt types.PatchType, data []byte, opts metav1.PatchOptions, subresources ...string) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n62: \tAgentRuntimeExpansion\n63: }\n64: ```\n65: \n66: REST resource plural: **`agentruntimes`**.\n67: \n68: ### `CodeInterpretersGetter` / `CodeInterpreterInterface` (`.../codeinterpreter.go`)\n69: \n70: Same method shape as `AgentRuntimeInterface`, types `*runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter` / `CodeInterpreterList`. REST resource plural: **`codeinterpreters`**.\n71: \n72: ### Expansion hooks (`generated_expansion.go`)\n73: \n74: ```go\n75: type AgentRuntimeExpansion interface{}\n76: type CodeInterpreterExpansion interface{}\n77: ```\n78: \n79: (Empty — reserved for custom methods.)\n80: \n81: ### Fake clients (`typed/runtime/v1alpha1/fake/`)\n82: \n83: `fake_runtime_client.go`, `fake_agentruntime.go`, `fake_codeinterpreter.go` — test doubles implementing the typed interfaces; `doc.go` markers.\n84: \n85: ---\n86: \n87: ## Scheme (`clientset/versioned/scheme/`)\n88: \n89: | File | Role |\n90: |------|------|\n91: | `register.go` | Builds `Scheme`, `Codecs`, `ParameterCodec`; `AddToScheme` registers `runtime/v1alpha1` types |\n92: | `doc.go` | Package doc |\n93: \n94: ---\n95: \n96: ## Informer factory\n97: \n98: ### `SharedInformerFactory` (`informers/externalversions/factory.go`)\n99: \n100: ```go\n101: type SharedInformerFactory interface {\n102: \tinternalinterfaces.SharedInformerFactory\n103: \tStart(stopCh <-chan struct{})\n104: \tShutdown()\n105: \tWaitForCacheSync(stopCh <-chan struct{}) map[reflect.Type]bool\n106: \tForResource(resource schema.GroupVersionResource) (GenericInformer, error)\n107: \tInformerFor(obj runtime.Object, newFunc internalinterfaces.NewInformerFunc) cache.SharedIndexInformer\n108: \tRuntime() externalversionsruntime.Interface\n109: }\n110: ```\n111: \n112: **Constructors / options**\n113: \n114: - `NewSharedInformerFactory(client versioned.Interface, defaultResync time.Duration)`\n115: - `NewSharedInformerFactoryWithOptions(client, defaultResync, options ...SharedInformerOption)`\n116: - `NewFilteredSharedInformerFactory` (deprecated alias to WithOptions)\n117: - Options: `WithCustomResyncConfig`, `WithTweakListOptions`, `WithNamespace`, `WithTransform`\n118: \n119: ### Group interface (`informers/externalversions/runtime/interface.go`)\n120: \n121: ```go\n122: type Interface interface {\n123: \tV1alpha1() v1alpha1.Interface\n124: }\n125: ```\n126: \n127: `New(factory, namespace, tweakListOptions)` returns group accessor.\n128: \n129: ### Version interface (`informers/externalversions/runtime/v1alpha1/interface.go`)\n130: \n131: ```go\n132: type Interface interface {\n133: \tAgentRuntimes() AgentRuntimeInformer\n134: \tCodeInterpreters() CodeInterpreterInformer\n135: }\n136: ```\n137: \n138: ### Per-type informers (`.../runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime.go`, `codeinterpreter.go`)\n139: \n140: Example (`AgentRuntimeInformer`):\n141: \n142: ```go\n143: type AgentRuntimeInformer interface {\n144: \tInformer() cache.SharedIndexInformer\n145: \tLister() runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeLister\n146: }\n147: ```\n148: \n149: Also provides `NewAgentRuntimeInformer`, `NewFilteredAgentRuntimeInformer`, and analogous constructors for CodeInterpreter.\n150: \n151: ### Generic resource routing (`informers/externalversions/generic.go`)\n152: \n153: `ForResource` switches on:\n154: \n155: - `v1alpha1.SchemeGroupVersion.WithResource(\"agentruntimes\")` → `f.Runtime().V1alpha1().AgentRuntimes().Informer()`\n156: - `...WithResource(\"codeinterpreters\")` → `...CodeInterpreters().Informer()`\n157: \n158: ### `internalinterfaces` (`informers/externalversions/internalinterfaces/factory_interfaces.go`)\n159: \n160: ```go\n161: type NewInformerFunc func(versioned.Interface, time.Duration) cache.SharedIndexInformer\n162: type SharedInformerFactory interface {\n163: \tStart(stopCh <-chan struct{})\n164: \tInformerFor(obj runtime.Object, newFunc NewInformerFunc) cache.SharedIndexInformer\n165: }\n166: type TweakListOptionsFunc func(*metav1.ListOptions)\n167: ```\n168: \n169: ---\n170: \n171: ## Listers (`listers/runtime/v1alpha1/`)\n172: \n173: ### `AgentRuntimeLister` / `AgentRuntimeNamespaceLister` (`agentruntime.go`)\n174: \n175: ```go\n176: type AgentRuntimeLister interface {\n177: \tList(selector labels.Selector) ([]*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n178: \tAgentRuntimes(namespace string) AgentRuntimeNamespaceLister\n179: \tAgentRuntimeListerExpansion\n180: }\n181: \n182: type AgentRuntimeNamespaceLister interface {\n183: \tList(selector labels.Selector) ([]*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n184: \tGet(name string) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n185: \tAgentRuntimeNamespaceListerExpansion\n186: }\n187: ```\n188: \n189: `NewAgentRuntimeLister` uses `runtimev1alpha1.Resource(\"agentruntime\").GroupResource()`.\n190: \n191: ### `CodeInterpreterLister` / `CodeInterpreterNamespaceLister` (`codeinterpreter.go`)\n192: \n193: Same pattern for `CodeInterpreter`; `NewCodeInterpreterLister` uses `Resource(\"codeinterpreter\").GroupResource()`.\n194: \n195: ### Expansion (`expansion_generated.go`)\n196: \n197: Empty expansion interfaces for listers and namespace listers (all four types).\n198: \n199: ---\n200: \n201: ## Fake clientset (`clientset/versioned/fake/`)\n202: \n203: | File | Role |\n204: |------|------|\n205: | `clientset_generated.go` | `NewSimpleClientset`, `NewClientset` — in-memory fake `Clientset` |\n206: | `register.go` | Scheme registration for fakes |\n207: | `doc.go` | Package doc |\n208: \n209: ---\n210: \n211: ## File index (all paths under `client-go/`)\n212: \n213: | Path | Role |\n214: |------|------|\n215: | `clientset/versioned/clientset.go` | `Clientset`, `Interface`, constructors |\n216: | `clientset/versioned/scheme/register.go` | Scheme / codecs for generated client |\n217: | `clientset/versioned/scheme/doc.go` | Doc |\n218: | `clientset/versioned/fake/clientset_generated.go` | Fake clientset implementation |\n219: | `clientset/versioned/fake/register.go` | Fake scheme wiring |\n220: | `clientset/versioned/fake/doc.go` | Doc |\n221: | `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/runtime_client.go` | `RuntimeV1alpha1Client`, `RuntimeV1alpha1Interface` |\n222: | `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime.go` | `AgentRuntimeInterface`, typed REST client |\n223: | `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter.go` | `CodeInterpreterInterface`, typed REST client |\n224: | `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/generated_expansion.go` | Expansion interfaces |\n225: | `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/doc.go` | Doc |\n226: | `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/fake/fake_runtime_client.go` | Fake runtime group client |\n227: | `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/fake/fake_agentruntime.go` | Fake AgentRuntime client |\n228: | `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/fake/fake_codeinterpreter.go` | Fake CodeInterpreter client |\n229: | `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/fake/doc.go` | Doc |\n230: | `informers/externalversions/factory.go` | `SharedInformerFactory`, options, `Start`/`Shutdown`/`WaitForCacheSync` |\n231: | `informers/externalversions/generic.go` | `GenericInformer`, `ForResource` |\n232: | `informers/externalversions/runtime/interface.go` | Group `runtime` informer accessor |\n233: | `informers/externalversions/runtime/v1alpha1/interface.go` | `v1alpha1` informer accessors |\n234: | `informers/externalversions/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime.go` | AgentRuntime informer + constructor |\n235: | `informers/externalversions/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter.go` | CodeInterpreter informer + constructor |\n236: | `informers/externalversions/internalinterfaces/factory_interfaces.go` | Small factory interface + `NewInformerFunc`, `TweakListOptionsFunc` |\n237: | `listers/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime.go` | `AgentRuntimeLister`, namespace lister |\n238: | `listers/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter.go` | `CodeInterpreterLister`, namespace lister |\n239: | `listers/runtime/v1alpha1/expansion_generated.go` | Lister expansion interfaces |\n240: \n241: **Regeneration:** `make gen-client` → `hack/update-codegen.sh` (`k8s.io/code-generator` v0.34.1, `--with-watch`, output package `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go`).\n\n(End of file - total 241 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# client-go library\n\nGenerated Kubernetes client code for API group **`runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` / `v1alpha1`**, module path **`github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go`**. Source reference: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/client-go/`.\n\n## Clientset\n\n### `Interface` (`clientset/versioned/clientset.go`)\n\n```go\ntype Interface interface {\n\tDiscovery() discovery.DiscoveryInterface\n\tRuntimeV1alpha1() runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Interface\n}\n```\n\n### `Clientset` struct\n\nEmbeds `*discovery.DiscoveryClient` and holds `runtimeV1alpha1 *runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Client`.\n\n**Constructors**","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/deployment/client-go.md","time":{"start":1775850377315,"end":1775850377328}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775850377333,"sessionID":"ses_287124991ffeRjQmm9oDsFsSrT","part":{"id":"prt_d78ee501f0012JJ6UYKsqcCGA7","messageID":"msg_d78ee1db5001iEpIZ7nMm728Rz","sessionID":"ses_287124991ffeRjQmm9oDsFsSrT","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-df80aeb36ac24379b52910fde0981b09","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/deployment/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/deployment/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-001 — CRD AgentRuntime Type Definition\n2: \n3: **Module:** `pkg/apis`  \n4: **Language:** Go  \n5: **Size:** S\n6: \n7: ---\n8: \n9: ## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n10: \n11: ### Requirement: Package structure and registration\n12: \n13: The system SHALL define the `AgentRuntime` and `AgentRuntimeList` types in `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/` with proper package structure, scheme registration, and CRD markers for controller-gen.\n14: \n15: #### Scenario: Package structure exists\n16: - **GIVEN** the repository root at `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube`\n17: - **WHEN** examining `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/`\n18: - **THEN** the directory SHALL contain:\n19:   - `doc.go` with `+k8s:deepcopy-gen=package` marker\n20:   - `register.go` with `SchemeGroupVersion` set to `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`\n21:   - `agentruntime_types.go` with `AgentRuntime` and `AgentRuntimeList` types\n22:   - `codeinterpreter_types.go` with `CodeInterpreter` and `CodeInterpreterList` types\n23:   - `zz_generated.deepcopy.go` (generated)\n24: \n25: #### Scenario: Scheme group version is correct\n26: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/register.go`\n27: - **WHEN** reading the file\n28: - **THEN** `SchemeGroupVersion` SHALL be `schema.GroupVersion{Group: \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\", Version: \"v1alpha1\"}`\n29: \n30: #### Scenario: Group version kind registration\n31: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/register.go`\n32: - **WHEN** the `addKnownTypes` function is invoked\n33: - **THEN** it SHALL register `AgentRuntime`, `AgentRuntimeList`, `CodeInterpreter`, and `CodeInterpreterList` with the scheme\n34: \n35: ---\n36: \n37: ### Requirement: AgentRuntime type definition\n38: \n39: The system SHALL define `AgentRuntime` as a Kubernetes-style typed object with `TypeMeta`, `ObjectMeta`, `Spec`, and `Status`.\n40: \n41: #### Scenario: AgentRuntime struct shape\n42: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types.go`\n43: - **WHEN** reading the `AgentRuntime` struct definition\n44: - **THEN** the struct SHALL embed `metav1.TypeMeta` and `metav1.ObjectMeta` and have `Spec AgentRuntimeSpec` and `Status AgentRuntimeStatus` fields with JSON tags `spec` and `status`\n45: \n46: #### Scenario: AgentRuntimeList struct shape\n47: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types.go`\n48: - **WHEN** reading the `AgentRuntimeList` struct definition\n49: - **THEN** the struct SHALL embed `metav1.TypeMeta`, have `metav1.ListMeta` with JSON tag `metadata`, and `Items []AgentRuntime` with JSON tag `items`\n50: \n51: #### Scenario: CRD markers on AgentRuntime\n52: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types.go`\n53: - **WHEN** examining type-level markers\n54: - **THEN** the `AgentRuntime` type SHALL have:\n55:   - `+genclient` marker\n56:   - `+k8s:deepcopy-gen:interfaces=k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime.Object` marker\n57:   - `+kubebuilder:object:root=true` marker\n58:   - `+kubebuilder:subresource:status` marker\n59: \n60: ---\n61: \n62: ### Requirement: AgentRuntimeSpec definition\n63: \n64: The system SHALL define `AgentRuntimeSpec` with required fields for session management and pod templating.\n65: \n66: #### Scenario: AgentRuntimeSpec fields\n67: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types.go`\n68: - **WHEN** reading the `AgentRuntimeSpec` struct\n69: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n70:   - `MaxSessionDuration string` with JSON tag `maxSessionDuration`\n71:   - `SessionTimeout string` with JSON tag `sessionTimeout`\n72:   - `TargetPort []TargetPort` with JSON tag `targetPort`\n73:   - `PodTemplate PodTemplateSpec` with JSON tag `podTemplate`\n74: \n75: #### Scenario: AgentRuntimeSpec required fields\n76: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types.go`\n77: - **WHEN** examining the `AgentRuntimeSpec` struct markers\n78: - **THEN** the struct SHALL have `+kubebuilder:validation:Required` or equivalent kubebuilder markers for `maxSessionDuration`, `sessionTimeout`, `targetPort`, and `podTemplate` fields\n79: \n80: #### Scenario: MaxSessionDuration default\n81: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types.go`\n82: - **WHEN** examining the `MaxSessionDuration` field marker\n83: - **THEN** it SHALL have `+kubebuilder:default=\"8h\"` marker\n84: \n85: #### Scenario: SessionTimeout default\n86: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types.go`\n87: - **WHEN** examining the `SessionTimeout` field marker\n88: - **THEN** it SHALL have `+kubebuilder:default=\"15m\"` marker\n89: \n90: ---\n91: \n92: ### Requirement: TargetPort type definition\n93: \n94: The system SHALL define `TargetPort` to specify how traffic is routed to the agent runtime pod.\n95: \n96: #### Scenario: TargetPort struct fields\n97: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types.go`\n98: - **WHEN** reading the `TargetPort` struct\n99: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain:\n100:   - `Port int32` with JSON tag `port` (required)\n101:   - `Protocol ProtocolType` with JSON tag `protocol` (enum: HTTP, HTTPS)\n102:   - `Name string` with JSON tag `name` (optional)\n103:   - `PathPrefix string` with JSON tag `pathPrefix` (optional)\n104: \n105: #### Scenario: ProtocolType enum definition\n106: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types.go`\n107: - **WHEN** reading the `ProtocolType` type definition\n108: - **THEN** it SHALL be a string type with `+kubebuilder:validation:Enum=HTTP;HTTPS` marker and constants `ProtocolHTTP` and `ProtocolHTTPS`\n109: \n110: ---\n111: \n112: ### Requirement: AgentRuntimeStatus definition\n113: \n114: The system SHALL define `AgentRuntimeStatus` with standard Kubernetes condition fields.\n115: \n116: #### Scenario: AgentRuntimeStatus fields\n117: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types.go`\n118: - **WHEN** reading the `AgentRuntimeStatus` struct\n119: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain `Conditions []metav1.Condition` with JSON tag `conditions`\n120: \n121: #### Scenario: Conditions field markers\n122: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types.go`\n123: - **WHEN** examining the `Conditions` field\n124: - **THEN** it SHALL have:\n125:   - `+kubebuilder:validation:Optional` marker\n126:   - `+listType=map` marker\n127:   - `+listMapKey=type` marker\n128: \n129: ---\n130: \n131: ### Requirement: DeepCopy generation\n132: \n133: The system SHALL generate `DeepCopy` methods for all types using controller-gen.\n134: \n135: #### Scenario: DeepCopyInto for AgentRuntime\n136: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/zz_generated.deepcopy.go` (after `make generate`)\n137: - **WHEN** examining generated code\n138: - **THEN** `func (in *AgentRuntime) DeepCopyInto(out *AgentRuntime)` SHALL exist and correctly copy all nested fields including `Spec.TargetPort` slice\n139: \n140: #### Scenario: DeepCopyInto for AgentRuntimeList\n141: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/zz_generated.deepcopy.go`\n142: - **WHEN** examining generated code\n143: - **THEN** `func (in *AgentRuntimeList) DeepCopyInto(out *AgentRuntimeList)` SHALL exist and correctly copy `Items` slice\n144: \n145: #### Scenario: DeepCopyInto for AgentRuntimeSpec\n146: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/zz_generated.deepcopy.go`\n147: - **WHEN** examining generated code\n148: - **THEN** `func (in *AgentRuntimeSpec) DeepCopyInto(out *AgentRuntimeSpec)` SHALL exist\n149: \n150: #### Scenario: DeepCopyInto for TargetPort\n151: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/zz_generated.deepcopy.go`\n152: - **WHEN** examining generated code\n153: - **THEN** `func (in *TargetPort) DeepCopyInto(out *TargetPort)` SHALL exist\n154: \n155: #### Scenario: DeepCopyInto for AgentRuntimeStatus\n156: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/zz_generated.deepcopy.go`\n157: - **WHEN** examining generated code\n158: - **THEN** `func (in *AgentRuntimeStatus) DeepCopyInto(out *AgentRuntimeStatus)` SHALL exist\n159: \n160: ---\n161: \n162: ### Requirement: CRD generation\n163: \n164: The system SHALL generate CRD YAML that matches the expected schema from `manifests/charts/base/crds/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_agentruntimes.yaml`.\n165: \n166: #### Scenario: CRD generation command\n167: - **GIVEN** the repository with types defined in `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/`\n168: - **WHEN** running `make gen-crd`\n169: - **THEN** the command SHALL invoke `controller-gen crd paths=./pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/... output:dir=manifests/charts/base/crds`\n170: \n171: #### Scenario: Generated CRD metadata\n172: - **GIVEN** the generated `manifests/charts/base/crds/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_agentruntimes.yaml`\n173: - **WHEN** examining the CRD\n174: - **THEN** `metadata.name` SHALL be `agentruntimes.runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`\n175: - AND `spec.group` SHALL be `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`\n176: - AND `spec.names.kind` SHALL be `AgentRuntime`\n177: - AND `spec.names.plural` SHALL be `agentruntimes`\n178: - AND `spec.scope` SHALL be `Namespaced`\n179: \n180: #### Scenario: Generated CRD version\n181: - **GIVEN** the generated CRD\n182: - **WHEN** examining `spec.versions`\n183: - **THEN** there SHALL be exactly one version with `name: v1alpha1`, `served: true`, and `storage: true`\n184: \n185: #### Scenario: Generated CRD spec schema\n186: - **GIVEN** the generated CRD\n187: - **WHEN** examining `spec.versions[0].schema.openAPIV3Schema.properties.spec`\n188: - **THEN** the `required` array SHALL include `maxSessionDuration`, `sessionTimeout`, `targetPort`, and `podTemplate`\n189: - AND `properties.maxSessionDuration.default` SHALL be `\"8h\"`\n190: - AND `properties.sessionTimeout.default` SHALL be `\"15m\"`\n191: \n192: #### Scenario: Generated CRD status subresource\n193: - **GIVEN** the generated CRD\n194: - **WHEN** examining `spec.versions[0]`\n195: - **THEN** `subresources.status` SHALL be present\n196: \n197: ---\n198: \n199: ### Requirement: Client-go code generation compatibility\n200: \n201: The system SHALL define types compatible with `k8s.io/code-generator` for generating typed clients, informers, and listers.\n202: \n203: #### Scenario: Group version registration for client-gen\n204: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/register.go`\n205: - **WHEN** reading the file\n206: - **THEN** `SchemeBuilder` SHALL be defined using `NewSchemeBuilder` and `AddToScheme` SHALL be exposed as `localSchemeBuilder.AddToScheme(scheme)`\n207: \n208: #### Scenario: Types implement runtime.Object\n209: - **GIVEN** the `AgentRuntime` and `AgentRuntimeList` types\n210: - **WHEN** the DeepCopy methods are generated\n211: - **THEN** both types SHALL implement `runtime.Object` interface via `DeepCopyObject()` method\n212: \n213: #### Scenario: Client generation command\n214: - **GIVEN** types in `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/`\n215: - **WHEN** running `make gen-client`\n216: - **THEN** `hack/update-codegen.sh` SHALL be invoked, which runs `k8s.io/code-generator` v0.34.1 with:\n217:   - `--with-watch` flag\n218:   - `--output-dir client-go`\n219:   - `--output-pkg github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go`\n220:   - Input API at `runtime/v1alpha1`\n221: \n222: #### Scenario: Generated typed client exists\n223: - **GIVEN** client-go code generation completed\n224: - **WHEN** examining `client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime.go`\n225: - **THEN** `AgentRuntimeInterface` SHALL define methods: `Create`, `Update`, `UpdateStatus`, `Delete`, `DeleteCollection`, `Get`, `List`, `Watch`, `Patch`\n226: \n227: #### Scenario: Generated informer exists\n228: - **GIVEN** client-go code generation completed\n229: - **WHEN** examining `client-go/informers/externalversions/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime.go`\n230: - **THEN** `AgentRuntimeInformer` interface SHALL define `Informer() cache.SharedIndexInformer` and `Lister() runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeLister`\n231: \n232: #### Scenario: Generated lister exists\n233: - **GIVEN** client-go code generation completed\n234: - **WHEN** examining `client-go/listers/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime.go`\n235: - **THEN** `AgentRuntimeLister` interface SHALL define `List(selector labels.Selector)` and `AgentRuntimes(namespace string)` methods\n\n(End of file - total 235 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-001 — CRD AgentRuntime Type Definition\n\n**Module:** `pkg/apis`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** S\n\n---\n\n## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n\n### Requirement: Package structure and registration\n\nThe system SHALL define the `AgentRuntime` and `AgentRuntimeList` types in `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/` with proper package structure, scheme registration, and CRD markers for controller-gen.\n\n#### Scenario: Package structure exists\n- **GIVEN** the repository root at `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube`\n- **WHEN** examining `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/`\n- **THEN** the directory SHALL contain:\n  - `doc.go` with `+k8s:deepcopy-gen=package` marker\n  - `register.go` with `SchemeGroupVersion` set to `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/deployment/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775850377318,"end":1775850377331}}}}
